<h2>Bug #2251</h2>

<div class="issue status-5 priority-4 priority-default closed details">

  <img alt="" class="gravatar" default="" rating="PG" src="http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/560785b80dbf9b35fcac5a7dbd6cdaf3?rating=PG&amp;size=50&amp;default=" ssl="false" title="" />

<div class="subject">
<div><h3>cron provider doesn&#x27;t correctly employ user property for resource existence checks.</h3></div>
</div>
        <p class="author">
        Added by <a href="/users/404" class="user active">Marc Fournier</a> <a href="/projects/puppet/activity?from=2009-05-13" title="05/12/2009 08:16 pm">over 4 years</a> ago.
        Updated <a href="/projects/puppet/activity?from=2013-04-18" title="04/18/2013 03:18 pm">4 months</a> ago.
        </p>

<table class="attributes">
<tr><th class="status">Status:</th><td class="status">Closed</td><th class="start-date">Start date:</th><td class="start-date">05/12/2009</td></tr><tr><th class="priority">Priority:</th><td class="priority">Normal</td><th class="due-date">Due date:</th><td class="due-date"></td></tr><tr><th class="assigned-to">Assignee:</th><td class="assigned-to">-</td><th class="progress">% Done:</th><td class="progress"><table class="progress" style="width: 80px;"><tr><td class="todo" style="width: 100%;"></td></tr></table><p class="pourcent">0%</p></td></tr><tr><th class="category">Category:</th><td class="category">cron</td><th></th><td></td></tr><tr><th class="fixed-version">Target version:</th><td class="fixed-version"><a href="/versions/371">3.2.0</a></td><th></th><td></td></tr>
<tr>
	<th>Affected Puppet version:</th><td>0.24.8</td>
	<th>Branch:</th><td>https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppet/pull/1582/files</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<th>Keywords:</th><td></td>
</tr>

    <tr><td><b>




    </td></tr>

</table>

<hr />
<div class="description">
  <div class="contextual">
  
  </div>

  <p><strong>Description</strong></p>
  <div class="wiki">
  <p>If I change the &ldquo;user&rdquo; parameter of a cron{} resource, the previous user will still have the cron listed in his crontab.</p>

<p>Assuming the resource name stays the same, I would have expected changing the &ldquo;user&rdquo; parameter to be as transparent as changing &ldquo;hour&rdquo;, &ldquo;minute&rdquo;, etc.</p>

<p>This is a possible workaround, but it may not be desirable in every case:</p>

<pre>
resource { "cron": purge => true }
</pre>


  </div>
</div>





