  <div id="change-28036" class="journal has-notes has-details">
    <div id="note-11">
    <h4><a href="/issues/2251#note-11" class="journal-link">#11</a>
    <img alt="" class="gravatar" default="" rating="PG" src="http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/702c996f0e78f2ebb05b927b115fa22b?rating=PG&amp;size=24&amp;default=" ssl="false" title="" />
    Updated by <a href="/users/380" class="user active">Nigel Kersten</a> <a href="/projects/puppet/activity?from=2011-03-31" title="03/30/2011 05:21 pm">over 2 years</a> ago</h4>

    <ul class="details">
       <li><strong>Subject</strong> changed from <i>cron doesn&#x27;t clean crontab when changing user</i> to <i>cron provider doesn&#x27;t correctly employ user property for resource existence checks.</i></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="wiki" id="journal-28036-notes"><p>user is actually a property of the provider, not a parameter, so we&rsquo;re not going to be automatically cleaning up crontab entries when you change user.</p>

<p>Think of packages. When you change a resource to install &lsquo;foo&rsquo; rather than &lsquo;bar&rsquo;, we don&rsquo;t uninstall &lsquo;bar&rsquo;.</p>

<p>There&rsquo;s definitely a bug here though, which I believe is captured by RI&rsquo;s update in note 4.</p>
</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
